# _local/ is the maintainer's private working area, and it is NOT version-controlled.
#
# It holds the 2026-07-10 audit corpus, session logs, and working notes. Until 2026-07-14 it
# was force-INCLUDED here (`!_local/`), because the library itself was still being built inside
# it. That is no longer true: the templates graduated to templates/ (decision 0009), and the
# planning and strategy docs the public README and methodology actually cite were promoted into
# docs/internal/ (decision 0013).
#
# Do not re-include it. The audit's adoption-kit is the concrete reason: it carries a competing
# STATE.md and eight superseded decision records in the bespoke pre-MADR format. Publishing them
# would put a second source of truth, and a set of stale ADRs in the one format the org forbids,
# into a public repo. See docs/internal/decisions/0011-madr-v4-at-docs-internal-decisions.md.
#
# The rule, so it does not have to be rediscovered: anything under _local/ that a tracked file
# needs must be PROMOTED into docs/internal/, never linked across the boundary. A tracked file
# linking into _local/ is a link that 404s for everyone but the maintainer, and CI fails on it.
#
# (Note: the maintainer's global gitignore already hides _LOCAL/ everywhere. This entry is
# explicit anyway, so a fresh clone on any machine behaves the same way.)
_local/

# Tool caches and OS junk.
.memsearch/
**/.impeccable/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# subagent-driven-development scratch ledger
.superpowers/
